---
import GuideLayout from "../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";
---

<GuideLayout
  title="Who to Give To"
  subtitle="The eight Quranic categories of Zakat recipients, ineligible parties, and practical distribution guidelines."
  chapter="Part Three — Chapter VI"
>
  <div class="space-y-12">
    <section>
      <div class="relative">
        <span class="section-number">VI</span>
        <h2 class="relative z-10 text-2xl mb-6">Giving Zakat</h2>
      </div>

      <p class="drop-cap text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-light mb-8">
        Knowing <em>how much</em> to give is only half the obligation.
        Knowing <em>who</em> to give to is equally important. The Quran
        specifies eight categories of eligible Zakat recipients in Surah
        At-Tawbah (9:60). Understanding these categories — and who is
        <em>not</em> eligible — ensures your Zakat fulfills its purpose.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Who NOT to Give To -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl mb-6">Who is <em>Not</em> Eligible</h2>
      <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Before discussing eligible recipients, it's important to understand who
        cannot receive Zakat:
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <div class="card bg-red-50/20 border-red-200/30">
          <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">1. The Rich</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-light">
            Those who already have sufficient means to cover their needs. A
            person with wealth above Nisab generally cannot receive Zakat.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card bg-red-50/20 border-red-200/30">
          <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">2. Able-Bodied Workers Who Can Earn</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-light">
            If employment opportunities are present, the work is permissible,
            and the person can perform it without undue hardship, they should
            work rather than receive Zakat.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card bg-red-50/20 border-red-200/30">
          <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">3. Your Immediate Dependents</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-light mb-2">
            You cannot give Zakat to people you are already financially
            responsible for. However, there are exceptions:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-ink-light text-sm space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>- Married daughters (husband is responsible for maintenance)</li>
            <li>- Spouses if needy (a wife is not obligated to maintain her husband)</li>
            <li>- Any family member you are <em>not</em> responsible for maintaining</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card bg-red-50/20 border-red-200/30">
          <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">4. Family of the Prophet Muhammad</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-light">
            Members of Banu Hashim and Banu Muttalib (the Prophet's clan) are
            traditionally ineligible for Zakat.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card bg-red-50/20 border-red-200/30">
          <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">5. Non-Muslims (Scholarly Difference)</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-light">
            Three scholarly positions exist: (a) never eligible, (b) only
            under the "softening hearts" category, (c) all categories if
            need exists and it doesn't deprive Muslims. Consult your scholar.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider-gold"></div>

    <!-- The Eight Categories -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl mb-4">The Eight Categories of Zakat Recipients</h2>
      <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-2">
        From Quran 9:60 — these are the <strong>only</strong> eligible
        recipients of Zakat:
      </p>
      <div class="card-gold mb-8">
        <p class="font-body italic text-forest-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          "Zakat expenditures are only for the poor and for the needy and
          for those employed for it and for bringing hearts together and
          for freeing captives and for those in debt and for the cause of
          Allah and for the stranded traveler — an obligation imposed by
          Allah. And Allah is Knowing and Wise."
        </p>
        <p class="font-ui text-xs text-ink-lighter mt-2">— Quran 9:60</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- 1. Al-Fuqara -->
        <div class="card">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-gold/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="font-display text-gold font-bold">1</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">
                Al-Fuqarā' — The Destitute
              </h4>
              <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed">
                Those who have absolutely nothing — in extreme need, unable to
                meet even the most basic necessities. They are in a more severe
                state than the poor (masakin).
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2. Al-Masakin -->
        <div class="card">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-gold/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="font-display text-gold font-bold">2</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">
                Al-Masākīn — The Poor
              </h4>
              <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed">
                The working poor — people who earn income but it is insufficient
                to cover their needs. They typically do not ask or beg. The
                "sufficient" threshold: anyone without adequate means for
                themselves and their dependents.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 3. Al-Amilin -->
        <div class="card">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-gold/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="font-display text-gold font-bold">3</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">
                Al-'Āmilīn 'Alaihā — Zakat Administrators
              </h4>
              <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-2">
                Those employed to collect, manage, and distribute Zakat. They
                must be trustworthy, intelligent, and knowledgeable Muslims.
              </p>
              <ul class="text-ink-lighter text-sm space-y-1">
                <li>- Maximum 1/8 of gross collected should pay administrators</li>
                <li>- Preferably from among the poor seeking work</li>
                <li>- Cannot accept personal gifts while in this role</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 4. Al-Muallafat -->
        <div class="card">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-gold/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="font-display text-gold font-bold">4</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">
                Al-Mu'allafat Qulūbuhum — Softening of Hearts
              </h4>
              <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed">
                Those whose faith needs to be preserved or strengthened — new
                converts, people with fragile faith, and programs that address
                anti-Muslim sentiment. This may require third-party vetting
                to verify the need.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 5. Fi'r-Riqab -->
        <div class="card">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-gold/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="font-display text-gold font-bold">5</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">
                Fī'r-Riqāb — Ending Human Subjugation
              </h4>
              <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed">
                Originally for freeing slaves (manumission). In the modern
                context, this extends to combating human trafficking, peonage,
                forced labor, and child labor — any effort to free people from
                subjugation and exploitation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 6. Al-Gharimin -->
        <div class="card">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-gold/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="font-display text-gold font-bold">6</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">
                Al-Ghārimīn — Those in Debt
              </h4>
              <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-2">
                People burdened by debts they cannot repay. This includes:
              </p>
              <ul class="text-ink-light text-sm space-y-1.5 mb-2">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gold mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
                  <span><strong>Personal debts:</strong> Medical bills, living paycheck to paycheck, unpaid bills</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gold mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
                  <span><strong>Collective debts:</strong> Natural disaster victims, community loans</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-ink-lighter text-sm">
                Conditions: They lack funds, the debt was for permissible purposes, and it is currently due.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 7. Fi Sabili'llah -->
        <div class="card">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-gold/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="font-display text-gold font-bold">7</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">
                Fī Sabīli'llāh — In God's Path
              </h4>
              <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-2">
                Traditionally: non-conscripted soldiers serving under a
                legitimate Muslim authority without a salary.
              </p>
              <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed">
                <strong>Modern expanded view:</strong> Any legitimate act that
                promotes Islam — Islamic education programs, media and
                outreach, community development, and scholarly work.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 8. Ibn As-Sabil -->
        <div class="card">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-gold/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-1">
              <span class="font-display text-gold font-bold">8</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-1">
                Ibn As-Sabīl — The Wayfarer
              </h4>
              <p class="text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-2">
                Travelers who find themselves without sufficient funds while
                away from home. Conditions:
              </p>
              <ul class="text-ink-lighter text-sm space-y-1">
                <li>- Must need assistance in their transient state</li>
                <li>- The travel must be for a permissible purpose</li>
                <li>- They have no other means available</li>
                <li>- Even wealthy travelers stranded without funds qualify</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider-gold"></div>

    <!-- Distribution Guidelines -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl mb-6">Distribution Guidelines</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="card">
          <ul class="text-ink-light space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold mt-2 shrink-0"></span>
              <span>There is <strong>no fixed percentage</strong> required per category. Distribute based on need.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold mt-2 shrink-0"></span>
              <span>The <strong>poor and destitute have priority</strong> — more dire needs take precedence.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold mt-2 shrink-0"></span>
              <span>It is <strong>better to empower</strong> than to hand out cash — help people become self-sufficient.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold mt-2 shrink-0"></span>
              <span>For categories 4–8, <strong>pay creditors or service providers directly</strong> rather than giving cash to the individual.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gold mt-2 shrink-0"></span>
              <span><strong>Document need</strong> with bills, receipts, and verification where possible.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider-gold"></div>

    <!-- Best Practices -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl mb-6">Best Practices</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Maximize Tax Benefits</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-light">
            Get receipts for all Zakat donations. In many countries, donations
            to registered charities are tax-deductible. This is a win-win —
            you fulfill your obligation and reduce your tax burden.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Corporate Matching</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-light">
            Many employers offer donation matching programs (1:1 or even 3:1).
            Check if your employer will match your Zakat donations — this
            multiplies the impact of your giving.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Know Your Community</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-light">
            Develop relationships with the poor in your own community. Direct,
            personal giving to those you know are in need is often more
            impactful than anonymous donations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h4 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Plan Ahead</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-light">
            Know your Zakat date, prepare your calculation in advance, and
            research recipients before the due date. Planning ensures your
            Zakat reaches the right people at the right time.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <div class="flex justify-between pt-8">
      <a href="/guide/earnings-expenses" class="group flex items-center gap-3 font-ui text-sm font-medium text-forest-600 hover:text-gold transition-colors">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
        </svg>
        <span>Previous: Earnings &amp; Expenses</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/calculator" class="group flex items-center gap-3 font-ui text-sm font-medium text-gold hover:text-gold-600 transition-colors">
        <span>Calculate Your Zakat</span>
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</GuideLayout>
